The paper focuses on the design and evaluation of an emulation framework for Fog Computing scenarios, which involves networking, distributed systems, and system architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the scalability and efficacy of the framework, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper deals with the design of Fog Computing infrastructures, which is related to cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing). The paper also discusses the emulation of real applications and workloads, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Docker-based applications, which is related to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
